narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: the first chance you really have to do a fully self-directed project. take the opportunity. you'll learn things you never could in an actual class setting, most of them about yourself, how you work, how you think, how you write; what you think is important.

Absolutely. If you are a humanities major, you will likely find that this is an incredible opportunity to bring to fruition the compilation of ideas and interests you've developed through the room that the Humanities major offers you to explore your own interests and desires. It can also be a way to develop a worthwhile and significant relationship with your adviser.
Absolutely. As an opportunity for free mental reign.

The senior essay in Humanities was for me a super challenging, incredibly valuable experience. Take advantage of it to really explore yourinterests. It is well-complemented by presenting at a senior Mellon Forum dinner.
This is a required part of the Humanities major -- so a 'recommendation' doesn't really make sense. Nonetheless, I would say it was very rewarding
Yes! Not that you have a choice if this is your major.
